            1147.0,
            968.0
          ],
          [
            1147.0,
            1282.0
          ],
          [
            620.0,
            1282.0
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "We use (Matsumoto et al., 2023), (Duan et al., 2023), (Kong et al., 2023) as our baseline methods. Since these work did not study the case of Diffusion Transformers, we integrate their algorithms into the DiT framework for evaluation. For the difference function  $ D(x, \\hat{x}) $, following the setup in (Duan et al., 2023; Kong et al., 2023), we take the L2 norm of  $ x - \\hat{x} $ to measure the differences between two",
